    <div class="card" id="SpendingSkillPoints">
        <h2>Spending Skill Points</h2>

        <p>
            Skills are like attributes but more specific to various situations. There are 6 skill groups, one for each attribute and, as a result, 
            each skill has a constituting attribute score. 
        </p>
        <p>
            Rather than having a pool of generic skill points to assign from, each character generates points into 6 groups, one for each attribute. 
            These skill points can only be spent on skills that are governed by the same attribute that generated the points. This means that if a 
            character has a Might score of 3, they would generate 3 Might Skill Points that can only be spent on Might Skills. Skill points are spent 
            one to one, so all points of each attribute can be spent on one skill or as many different skills as the player has points for, within 
            the attribute’s skill options. The only stipulation, however, is that a skill’s score cannot exceed the score of its governing attribute. 
            If a situation is created where that one rule must be broken for all skill points to be spent, the unspent skills points are instead lost, so allocate wisely!
        </p>
